version_description: Easy way to play "Arms open" CAPO 3.
Putting capo on the first fret makes it a lot easier to play the song. Any guitar player can play this song as the chord pattern is super easy.
This version has a more accurate timing with chord changes at beat "1" and "2 AND" as well as more accurate chords.
This tab uses simple chords and does not require a capo.
This tab uses the simplest chords possible and requires a capo on the 1st fret.
This is the chords that fit to the song. Sounds almost perfect to the song.
First version of this song. No Capo required. Can be plucked or strummed.
